The paper discusses mechanism design for facility games, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS) for designing social choice mechanisms. The focus on approximation mechanisms suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for designing algorithms that learn and adapt to the behavior of agents. Finally, the use of metrics and optimization criteria suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
